<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-0572 </DOCNO><TEXT>While numerous studies of the NATO Alliance have been published over theyears, few of these volumes consider wider foreign policy issues. USForeign Policy and European Security fills the gap by relating broaderpolitical and economic factors to military security considerations withinthe NATO Alliance and the related Atlantic area nations. This study offersan extensive discussion of the development of Atlantic relationshipsover time, including evolutionary trends and the major Post-World WarII events which led to the formation of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.</TEXT></DOC>